    "kernel": "6.17.0-22-generic",
    "notes": "**Broken after April 21, 2026 update -- game does not launch**\n\n**System:**\n- OS: Linux Mint 22.3 Cinnamon 64-bit\n- Kernel: 6.17.0-22-generic\n- GPU: AMD Radeon RX 7600M XT (amdgpu/Mesa)\n- Proton versions tested: Experimental (11.0-20260417), 10.0-4, 9.0-4, GE-Proton (latest)\n\n**Symptoms:**\nAfter the April 21, 2026 update, the game no longer launches. Steam shows a brief CPU spike (~10%), then the process freezes before the game window appears. No crash dialog, no error message.\n\n**Diagnosis:**\nTwo issues were found during investigation:\n\n1. **installscript.vdf blocks launch** -- The script attempts to run DXSETUP.exe (DirectX Jun2010) on every launch. Under Linux this process hangs indefinitely, preventing Proton from ever starting. Workaround: rename installscript.vdf to installscript.vdf.bak.\n\n2. **Wine exits silently after Proton initializes** -- Even with PROTON_LOG=1 and WINEDEBUG=+loaddll,+module, the log only contains the Proton header. Wine exits before loading a single DLL. No segfault, no OOM kill, no kernel error (dmesg clean). This appears to be a regression introduced by the April 21 update, possibly related to the newly added libcef.dll (95MB Chromium Embedded Framework).\n\n**Workarounds attempted (none resolved issue 2):**\n- Full reinstall + file verification\n- Deleting compatdata (1151340)\n- Multiple Proton versions including GE-Proton\n- kernel.split_lock_mitigate=0\n- Various launch options\n\n**Status: Broken.** A fix likely requires a Proton update to handle the new CEF dependency introduced with this patch.",
